The convert_html_color_to_dec_array() method only returns the response in array format.

commit.message:
Fix X position of li tag

Fixed a problem in which the X position of a `li` tag is misaligned when there is an `input` tag in the form `<li><input type="checkbox">bar`.

Support GitHub Flavored Markdown Task list items (extension)

https://github.github.com/gfm/#task-list-items-extension-

[Changed]
Set a random string as the default value for the name attribute of the Input tag in the checkbox attribute.
Because the name variable in CheckBox() method must be a unique string.

No use NeedAppearances (default: false)

[Why]
If NeedAppearances=true, the states of CheckBox, etc and other items are not reflected,
so set NeedAppearances=false and implement the drawing process for each.

See: https://opensource.adobe.com/dc-acrobat-sdk-docs/pdfstandards/PDF32000_2008.pdf

> A flag specifying whether to construct appearance streams and appearance dictionaries for all widget annotations in the document (see 12.7.3.3, “Variable Text”).
> Default value: false

HTML tag Boolean Attribute supported

See: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Boolean/HTML

XHTML Form support

Some support for XHTML forms (see example n. 54).

Javascript Form and user rights support

- Some support for Forms fields (see example n. 14).
- addJavascriptObject() method was added.

FYI:
- getAnnotOptFromJSProp
  See:
    - prop(javascript field properties) : https://opensource.adobe.com/dc-acrobat-sdk-docs/library/jsapiref/JS_API_AcroJS.html
    - /Ff : https://www.pdf-tools.trustss.co.jp/Syntax/form.html
- AcroForm
  See:  https://opensource.adobe.com/dc-acrobat-sdk-docs/pdfstandards/PDF32000_2008.pdf
- Button : Flags for submit-form actions
  See: https://opensource.adobe.com/dc-acrobat-sdk-docs/pdfstandards/PDF32000_2008.pdf
- putannotsobjs : Annotation Flags
  See:
    - https://opensource.adobe.com/dc-acrobat-sdk-docs/pdfstandards/PDF32000_2008.pdf
    - https://www.pdf-tools.trustss.co.jp/Syntax/annot.html#f_entry
fix: comment format
fix indent
